  "response": "Here are a few great small batch chocolate chip cookie recipes:\n\n1. Classic Small Batch Recipe (Makes 6-8 cookies):\n- 1/4 cup butter\n- 1/4 cup brown sugar\n- 2 tbsp white sugar\n- 1 egg yolk\n- 1/2 tsp vanilla\n- 1/2 cup flour\n- 1/4 tsp baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips\n\n2. Soft and Chewy Version:\n- 1/4 cup butter\n- 1/3 cup brown sugar\n- 1 egg yolk\n- 1/2 tsp vanilla\n- 1/2 cup + 2 tbsp flour\n- 1/4 tsp baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/3 cup chocolate chips\n\n3. Healthier Options:\n- Use whole wheat flour\n- Substitute some butter with applesauce\n- Use dark chocolate chips\n- Add nuts for extra nutrition\n\nTips:\n- Chill dough for 30 minutes\n- Use room temperature ingredients\n- Bake at 350\u00b0F for 8-10 minutes\n- Let cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these recipes?",
